  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Severe sepsis induces significant changes in expression of insulin- and toll-like receptors,
      cytokines, markers of apoptosis, and activation of t- and b-lymphocytes.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      In patients at early stage of severe sepsis, we investigate the expression of pro- and
      anti-inflammatory cytokines, chemokines, adhesion-molecules, toll-like receptors,
      insulin-receptors, markers of apoptosis und of t- and b-cell-activation on a mRNA level.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
